results.name: Number of nonsquare divisors of n.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: a(36)=5 because the set of divisors of 36 has tau(36)=nine elements, {1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 9, 12, 18, 36}, five of which, that is {2, 3, 6, 12, 18}, are not perfect squares.
mathematica: a[1] = 0; a[n_] := Times @@ (1 + (e = Last /@ FactorInteger[n])) - Times @@ (1 + Floor[e/2]); Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2019 *)
xref: See A194095 and A194096 for record values and where they occur.
